MF=1   General Information                                         325 1451   66
 MT=451 Descriptive Data                                           325 1451   67
    The neutron emission reaction channels for incident alpha      325 1451   68
    particle energy below 15 MeV are given in the following table. 325 1451   69
                                                                   325 1451   70
   Reaction    Q-value (MeV)     Threshold Energy (MeV)            325 1451   71
    (a,n)       -3.974                 6.621                       325 1451   72
    (a,pn)      -3.791                 6.313                       325 1451   73
    (a,a'n)     -5.664                 9.433                       325 1451   74
                                                                   325 1451   75
MF=3   Cross Sections                                              325 1451   76
 MT=201 Neutron Production Cross Section                           325 1451   77
    Mehta et al./1/ measured a relative excitation function at     325 1451   78
    forward angle (0+/-15deg.). They also measured angular dstri-  325 1451   79
    butions of neutrons at Ea=10,12 and 14 MeV. The angular dist-  325 1451   80
    ributions were well reproduced by calculation with a modified  325 1451   81
    EXIFON code (named "mEXIFON")/2/ using Kalbach's systematics   325 1451   82
    /3/ assuming the (a,n) reaction is caused by the multistep     325 1451   83
    compound process and the (a,pn) reaction is by multistep       325 1451   84
    direct process. Presumably the ground state of Li-6 has large  325 1451   85
    component of He-4+deuteron, and the deuteron dissociate into   325 1451   86
    n+p by direct recoil caused by incident alpha particle.        325 1451   87
    The experimental forward angle excitation function was con-    325 1451   88
    verted to the angle integrated excitation function using the   325 1451   89
    calculated angular distributions. The absolute cross section   325 1451   90
    was determined to reproduce the experimental thick target      325 1451   91
    neutron yield measured by Bair and Gomez del Campo/4/. Thick   325 1451   92
    target neutron yield was calculated using alpha particle stop- 325 1451   93
    ping power given by Ziegler/5/.                                325 1451   94
                                                                   325 1451   95
 MT=4, 22, 28   (a,n), (a,a'n), (a,pn)                             325 1451   96
    The ratio of each cross section of neutron emission to         325 1451   97
    neutron production cross section was calculated with the mEXI- 325 1451   98
    FON code and each cross section was calculated by multiplying  325 1451   99
    the ratio to the evaluated neutron production cross section.   325 1451  100
                                                                   325 1451  101
 MT=50, 51, 52, 53, 91  (a,n0), (a,n1), (a,n2), (a,n3), (a,nc)     325 1451  102
    The ratios of partial (a,ni) cross section to (a,n) cross      325 1451  103
    section were calculated with a statistical model code of       325 1451  104
    Hauser-Feshbach type and partial cross sections were obtained  325 1451  105
    by multiplying the ratio to the evaluated (a,n) cross section  325 1451  106
    for the following levels of B-9.                               325 1451  107
                                                                   325 1451  108
             Level     Ex(MeV)   Spin-Parity                       325 1451  109
              GS       0.0          3/2-                           325 1451  110
              1st      1.6          1/2+                           325 1451  111
              2nd      2.361        5/2-                           325 1451  112
              3rd      2.788        5/2+                           325 1451  113
                                                                   325 1451  114
        The levels above 4.8 MeV are assumed to be continuum.      325 1451  115
                                                                   325 1451  116
MF=6   Neutron Energy-angle Distributions (law=1, lang=2)          325 1451  117
 MT=4, 22, 28                                                      325 1451  118
    Emitted neutron contineous energy spectrum were calculated     325 1451  119
    with the mEXIFON code for each reaction. Multistep direct      325 1451  120
    reaction ratios of Kalbach's systematics are also given.       325 1451  121
